00:19:51.010 --> 00:19:52.010
Thanks."

00:19:52.010 --> 00:19:54.040
This is a great question.

00:19:56.960 --> 00:20:07.300
So I think that when you ask how do you know
whether a design idea works or not, another

00:20:07.300 --> 00:20:14.420
thing that I love about Exhibition Design
and especially here at MoMA is that it's a

00:20:14.420 --> 00:20:16.920
very rapid process.

00:20:19.150 --> 00:20:26.720
Relative to other design processes where you're
putting out a product, like we very quickly

00:20:26.730 --> 00:20:28.380
iterate through ideas.

00:20:28.380 --> 00:20:32.260
So I think we take a very experimental approach.

00:20:32.260 --> 00:20:41.230
So I feel like a design is successful when
we've honored an artist's vision or when we

00:20:41.230 --> 00:20:42.830
tried an idea in earnestness.

00:20:42.830 --> 00:20:46.280
We've pushed it as far as we could.

00:20:47.760 --> 00:20:57.920
In terms of like if it's failed, I don't know
if I can say that it's a failure if we went

00:20:57.920 --> 00:21:02.640
through a very thoughtful considered process
and we kind of pushed it as far as we could

00:21:02.640 --> 00:21:03.670
go with it.

00:21:03.670 --> 00:21:09.680
I don't consider, like even if it's a critical
failure for instance, if nobody likes it,

00:21:09.680 --> 00:21:15.330
or if the press pans it, I still
feel like it's been a success for us.

00:21:15.330 --> 00:21:20.530
I mean, I still feel if we've learned something
from it, if we've pushed an idea, if we took

00:21:20.530 --> 00:21:25.040
a chance, if we took a risk, then it's successful.

00:21:25.040 --> 00:21:26.040
Yeah.

00:21:26.040 --> 00:21:27.040
Did you...

00:21:27.040 --> 00:21:28.040
Yeah.

00:21:28.040 --> 00:21:34.370
I think also one of the great things about what
we do is we get to see whether or not it works.

00:21:36.670 --> 00:21:42.660
Something we tried and we're hoping that visitors
would choose to make this extra turn and it

00:21:42.660 --> 00:21:46.360
turns out most of them didn't and so this
corner of the gallery ended up being emptier

00:21:46.360 --> 00:21:47.530
or less viewed

00:21:48.720 --> 00:21:49.900
We learned something.

00:21:49.920 --> 00:21:53.380
As you said, that's something we learn from,
and actually getting to be in the space and

00:21:53.380 --> 00:21:58.370
see how people interact with it was amazing.

00:21:58.370 --> 00:22:00.880
And the critique is part of the process.

00:22:00.880 --> 00:22:03.170
I think that we invite critique.

00:22:03.170 --> 00:22:07.180
I know nothing we put out there is
going to be absolutely perfect.

00:22:07.180 --> 00:22:13.960
I think that if we can keep listening and keep
open, then I think it's a successful process.

00:22:14.620 --> 00:22:18.920
And if you see that something is unsuccessful
before we open and we have a chance to fix

00:22:18.920 --> 00:22:21.640
it, we do. Yes, this is true.

00:22:22.660 --> 00:22:23.660
What's next?

00:22:25.240 --> 00:22:28.460
Should we pick from here?

00:22:29.340 --> 00:22:30.760
All right.

